voke discussion. The book also includes a guide to resources available for the study of regional dialects in England. Key FeaturesAn up-to-date account of research into regional variation in EnglandA practical, 'hands on' approach, providing the reader with the methods and resources to carry out research projectsIncludes exercises for use in class.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aEnglish languagexDialectszGreat Britain. 4aLanguage & Linguistics. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-2000z978311078046840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978074862937440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780748629374423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780748629374/original  a978-3-11-078046-8  Edinburgh University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-2000c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK